<section class="section" style="padding-top:56px;">
  <div class="card pad" style="max-width:640px;margin:0 auto;">
    <div class="topbar" style="margin-bottom:14px;">
      <div>
        <div class="h-eyebrow">
          <span class="chip">Device</span>
          <span class="chip">Verification</span>
        </div>
        <h2 style="margin:10px 0 0;">Unable to confirm device</h2>
        <div class="small" style="margin-top:6px;">
          Store: <b><%= store.name %></b>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="notice" style="margin:12px 0; background:#f8faf9;">
      <div style="font-weight:900;">What happened</div>
      <div class="small" style="margin-top:6px;">
        After multiple attempts, we were unable to verify this device.
      </div>
      <div class="small" style="margin-top:6px;">
        This employee account is already linked to another device, or this browser data was reset.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="card pad" style="background:#fff;">
      <div style="font-weight:900;">What to do next</div>
      <div class="small" style="margin-top:6px;">
        Please contact your <b>Admin</b> or <b>Manager</b> and ask them to reset your device access.
      </div>
      <div class="small" style="margin-top:6px;">
        Once reset, scan the QR again and log in normally.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="small" style="margin-top:12px; text-align:center; color:#777;">
      If you believe this is a mistake, ask your Admin to review the attendance logs.
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
